{
  "texts": [
    "Generative AI tools could be used to create high-quality images of orthopedic diseases and anatomical structures, allowing for the visualization of concepts such as fracture types or joint replacements.",
    "These images can be suitable for teaching and case-based learning.",
    "Future studies should explore the potential and effectiveness of text-to-image generative AI tools in producing high-quality, clinically accurate images for orthopedic education.",
    "Utilizing image processing capabilities of generative AIWith the release of generative AI models such as GPT-4, which can now handle image inputs such as photographs, screenshots, and hand-drawn drawings, potential applications for medical education are rising [17].",
    "Although this feature remains in its early stage, it enables for the interpretation of relevant information from visual inputs."
  ]
}